<paragraph blockId="10.[827,1442,1645,1851]" pageId="10">
<emphasis box="[827,1165,1645,1667]" italics="true" pageId="10">Comments on karyotypes:</emphasis>
The meioformula of 
<taxonomicName authority="(Fabricius, 1775)" baseAuthorityName="Fabricius" baseAuthorityYear="1775" box="[827,1378,1676,1698]" class="Insecta" family="Hydrophilidae" genus="Tropisternus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="10" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="lateralis">
<emphasis box="[827,1129,1676,1698]" italics="true" pageId="10">Tropisternus lateralis</emphasis>
(Fabricius, 1775)
</taxonomicName>
was published by 
<bibRefCitation author="Smith SG" box="[986,1131,1706,1729]" pageId="10" pagination="31 - 48" refId="ref22581" refString="Smith SG. 1953. Chromosome numbers of Coleoptera. Heredity 7: 31 - 48." type="journal article" year="1953">Smith (1953</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Smith SG" box="[1146,1202,1706,1728]" pageId="10" pagination="66 - 88" refId="ref22598" refString="Smith SG. 1960. Chromosome numbers of Coleoptera II. Canadian Journal of Genetics and Cytogenetics 2: 66 - 88." type="journal article" year="1960">1960</bibRefCitation>
), the karyotype and meiosis of 
<taxonomicName authority="d'Orchymont, 1921" authorityName="d'Orchymont" authorityYear="1921" box="[953,1442,1737,1759]" class="Insecta" family="Hydrophilidae" genus="Tropisternus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="10" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="mutatus">
<emphasis box="[953,1210,1738,1759]" italics="true" pageId="10">Tropisternus mutatus</emphasis>
d’Orchymont, 1921
</taxonomicName>
was studied by 
<bibRefCitation author="Pine MB &amp; Gallo RB &amp; Clarkson B &amp; Ferreira N &amp; DaRosa R" box="[1023,1238,1768,1790]" pageId="10" pagination="243 - 248" refId="ref22011" refString="Pine MB, Gallo RB, Clarkson B, Ferreira N, DaRosa R. 2013. Evolutionary dynamics of Tropisternus karyotype (Coleoptera: Hydrophilidae: Hydrophilini) from southern Brazil. Cytologia 78: 243 - 248." type="journal article" year="2013">
Pine 
<emphasis box="[1088,1151,1768,1790]" italics="true" pageId="10">et al.</emphasis>
(2013)
</bibRefCitation>
. Published data indicate that 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Solier" authorityYear="1834" box="[996,1151,1799,1820]" class="Insecta" family="Hydrophilidae" genus="Tropisternus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="10" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[996,1151,1799,1820]" italics="true" pageId="10">Tropisternus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, like 
<taxonomicName authorityName="SOLIER" authorityYear="1834" box="[1222,1383,1799,1820]" class="Insecta" family="Hydrophilidae" genus="Sternolophus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="10" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1222,1383,1799,1820]" italics="true" pageId="10">Sternolophus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, has 2 
<emphasis box="[841,856,1830,1851]" italics="true" pageId="10">n</emphasis>
= 16 + Xy
</paragraph>
<paragraph box="[974,982,1845,1857]" pageId="10">p</paragraph>
